            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>I am (property) of Ietros.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="ru">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>It is possible that the name of Apollo was also included in the lost part of the inscription, 
                    but the divine epiclesis could also be used on its own (see e.g. XXX). The epigraphic form of 'speaking object' is common 
                in the Archaic period.
                
                The cult of Ietros was prominent in several Milesian apoikiai of the Black Sea, including... Ietros is one of the earliest attested deities
                worshipped in Borysthenes. So far, the cult has not been attested in Miletus itself (CHECK), and it remains a puzzling fact that several Pontic 
                colonies should have adopted a cultic epiclesis not known in the metropolis. Ietros was also prominent in Olbia: the earliest attestation there is
                dated to xx BCE. <!-- See Tokhtasiev's edition and discussion. --></p>
            </div>
